				<description>The speculative value of bitcoin itself is extremely valuable.

Think about Macao and Las Vegas, cities that both thrive on nothing but gambling. Are these cities not creating revenue?

Now think of all the world's stock markets? Do these exchange not profit just on people speculating?

Now think of a global currency like Bitcoin and its variants. I can loan, short, buy futures, buy GHs rate, buy alt-coins, etc... a multitude of ways to speculate on alternative sides. When someone for example buys a Tesla using Bitcoins, he actually sells Bitcoins. When miners mine Bitcoins and sell to pay for their hardware and energy costs, they actually sell Bitcoins. Bitcoins are sold almost every day, yet the price keeps going up? That is because speculation has value and speculation with high returns have even more value in this fiscal environment with paltry interest rates.

The current world situation in fact is position for Bitcoin to really explode. The lack of trust in the USD. The financial controls in China. The European crisis and the confiscation of money in Cyprus. The billions of unbanked people of the world. The paltry returns on both loans. 

Now your telling me that some economics ivory tower dude who can't grasp the abstraction is asking for a floor? What is the floor for the gambling cities of Macao and Las Vegas? Does gambling create anything useful???</description>                            
